        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "Pericytes , as a key cellular part of the blood - brain barrier , play an important role in the maintenance of brain neurovascular unit . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "These cells participate in brain homeostasis",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "by regulating vascular development and integrity mainly through secreting various factors . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "Pericytes per se show different restorative properties after blood - brain barrier injury . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Upon the occurrence of brain acute and chronic diseases , pericytes provoke immune cells to regulate neuro - inflammatory conditions . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "Loss of pericytes in distinct neurologic disorders intensifies blood - brain barrier permeability",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "and leads to vascular dementia . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "The therapeutic potential of pericytes is originated from the unique morphological shape , location , and their ability",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "in providing vast paracrine and juxtacrine interactions . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "A subset of pericytes possesses multipotentiality",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "and exhibit trans - differentiation capacity in the context of damaged tissue . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "This review article aimed to highlight the critical role of pericytes in restoration of the blood - brain barrier after injury",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "by focusing on the dynamics of pericytes and cross - talk with other cell types . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        }
    ]
